## 11. Non-negotiable rules

- Never skip planning.
- Never edit files before plan approval.
- Never claim success without validation.
- Never mark task `ready` unless validation exits cleanly.
- Never apply task changes without checkpointing.
- Never hide backend `409` transition errors.
- Never delete unrelated files.
- Never overwrite user work without review.
- Always keep Python schema and generated TypeScript types synchronized.
- Always run relevant tests after changes.

---

## 12. Definition of ready for the advanced coder-agent system

The system is ready when:

- user can create a plan from the UI
- user can revise and approve the plan
- approved plan creates queued tasks
- user can start a task
- task runs in isolated workspace
- task logs stream or refresh in UI
- task diff appears in UI
- validation output appears in UI
- failed validation keeps task failed
- clean validation marks task ready
- user can apply ready task
- checkpoint is created
- rollback works
- all tests/builds pass
- final response reports only verified success

Final clean state must include:

```text
NO ERROR
```
